de.saxsys.mvvmfx

Class FluentViewLoader.JavaViewStep<ViewType extends JavaView<? extends ViewModelType>,ViewModelType extends ViewModel>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.saxsys.mvvmfx.FluentViewLoader.JavaViewStep<ViewType,ViewModelType>
  • Type Parameters:
    ViewType - the generic type of the View that should be loaded. This type has to implement JavaView.
    ViewModelType - the generic type of the ViewModel. This type has to implement ViewModel.
    Enclosing class:
    FluentViewLoader

    public static class FluentViewLoader.JavaViewStep<ViewType extends JavaView<? extends ViewModelType>,ViewModelType extends ViewModel>
extends Object
    This class is the builder step to load a java based view. It is accessed from the FluentViewLoader with the method FluentViewLoader.javaView(Class).

      • resourceBundle

        public FluentViewLoader.JavaViewStep<ViewType,ViewModelType> resourceBundle(ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
        Provide a ResourceBundle that is used while loading this view. Note: It is possible to provide a global application-wide resourceBundle via MvvmFX.setGlobalResourceBundle(ResourceBundle) method.

        If there is a global resourceBundle set it will be merged with the resourceBundle provided by this builder method. The resourceBundle provided by this method will have a higher priority then the global one which means that if there are duplicate keys, the values of the global resourceBundle will be overwritten and the values of this resourceBundle will be used.

        It is possible to add multiple resourceBundles by invoking this builder method multiple times. In this case the last provided resourceBundle will have the highest priority when it comes to overwriting values with the same keys.

        Parameters:
        resourceBundle - the resource bundle that is used while loading the view.
        Returns:
        this instance of the builder step.

      • viewModel

        public FluentViewLoader.JavaViewStep<ViewType,ViewModelType> viewModel(ViewModelType viewModel)
        This param is used to define an existing viewModel instance to be used when loading the view.
        A typical use case is when you like to have two or more views that are sharing the same viewModel.
        Parameters:
        viewModel - the viewModel instance that is used to load the java view.
        Returns:
        this instance of the builder step.

      • codeBehind

        public FluentViewLoader.JavaViewStep<ViewType,ViewModelType> codeBehind(ViewType codeBehind)
        This param is used to define an existing instance of the codeBehind class that is used instead of creating a new one while loading.
        This can be useful when creating custom controls.
        Parameters:
        codeBehind - the codeBehind instance that is used to load this java view.
        Returns:
        this instance of the builder step.

        Returns:
